{
  "texts": [
    "The preprocessed images were then coregistered to its corresponding anatomical template (already in MNI space) 67, resampled to a 1.5 mm 3 voxel size and eventually corrected for bias field inhomogeneities 66.",
    "After motion correction as well as registration to the MNI template, the B-matrix was appropriately rotated 72.",
    "Functional data was preprocessed with fMRIprep 73 and the eXtensible Connectivity Pipeline (XCP-D) 74 which are two BIDS-compatible apps that perform all recommended processing steps to correct for distortion artifacts in functional data.",
    "Regression of global signal has been shown to improve denoising in BOLD series without excessive loss of community structure 75.",
    "In total, 36 nuisance regressors were selected from the nuisance confound matrices of fMRIPrep output which included six motion parameters, global signal, the mean white matter, the mean CSF signal with their temporal derivatives, and the quadratic expansion of six motion parameters, tissues signals and their temporal derivatives 76."
  ]
}